reviews.text: Excellent modern French. All dishes are great, and some are stunning. The scallops in fried bun is very special. The sake steamed fish is super tender. The wagyne beef with caviar is perfectly done. We ordered the 7 course tasting menu and the portion is just right. Definitely a must try!
Definitely a classic fine dining but if subject to a high end standard, their overall performance is just OK.
Great Somm.  Food trendiness was pushing it a bit too much,  lots of show for the fun,  a bit too fusion.   I recommend nonetheless.  Should close the balcony doors when hot.  Good experience

Blown away. Michelin Two Star. The chef from Amber. The food was as priced. Expensive and high quality, nice view. Could use a better service.

I liked their bar Piqniq. Can we have some style on our way to the rooftop bar?
Very tasty quality food,  but took us 3 and a half hour for a dinner.  Would be perfect if the time could reduce to 2 hours.

reviews.text: With excellent art throughout the year , the galleries here are always chopping and changing something new every few months. A real eclectic mix of artists; some well known, others less so, there's also piqnic on the roof for a well earned bevy.

The art was great but the accessibility of the building is horrible. I injured my knee and ankle earlier in the day and despite having a visible limp, the guards had to be asked repeatedly for the lift and only begrudgingly called for the elevator when I was going 3 and 5 floors down. For single floors I just hobbled down because they made such a big production out of it when I was going multiple floors.
Nice building. The janitors downstairs, they are a little pushy because of the crowd they get.
Very very great place to visit. And of cuz to see art and buy art.
House the majority of the quality art galleries  of Hong Kong
